Notebook[{
Cell["Euclidean Geometry", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"231a3958-3ea8-41a9-96f4-9b221fc73c7f"],

Cell["\<\
The Euclidean layer reconstructs Euclidean concepts -- point, segment, line, \
shell, circle, parallel, midpoint, perpendicular, bisector -- as graph \
properties under the infra-observer's standpoint. Every constructor returns a \
wrapped Infra* multi-realisation object; predicates test the corresponding \
pattern.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"effc5b16-a86a-4cd1-856f-ad3010e09551"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"5e43fb6f-ab02-4427-82a6-41e1960b3b79"],

Cell["Load the paclet.", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"ed9be9be-38a5-4a46-811d-d811defc907b"],

Cell["Needs[\"WolframInstitute`SyntheticInfrageometry`\"]", "Code",ExpressionUUID->"9acba5e1-b0a7-4dc3-a74e-187dabb6e387"],

Cell["Primitive postulates", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"0c958286-655e-41a9-9d86-b8dcadf87192"],

Cell["FindPoint", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"ce0dcac9-53e0-4081-a27b-d1103afc422f"],

Cell["FindSegment", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"730ce996-aa41-4843-b446-5a78dbf45402"],

Cell["FindLine", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"89d3d575-9e70-439c-aa82-ad79eea1e50e"],

Cell["ExtendSegment", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"514a8be0-7259-4868-a410-c747ffca7716"],

Cell["FindShell", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"bd59c09e-5249-4e52-ad0b-44491faa8e66"],

Cell["FindCircle", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"f175697c-53b2-4905-b61a-b38ba4d88296"],

Cell["FindParallel", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"8051f9f7-e643-42cb-a2c4-5806916f1ae0"],

Cell["Predicates", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"b3e46e09-2015-4e78-89db-8654157aaa9f"],

Cell["SegmentQ", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"785572ab-fc4d-4857-9532-aebe7df137d5"],

Cell["LineQ", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"d4488f7e-bdf8-4cf4-b358-890d416efe9c"],

Cell["ShellQ", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"4686227f-75d1-46e1-b958-d857d13c12d5"],

Cell["CircleQ", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"463ba2c8-9a9f-41e9-95e6-8e4c086ad516"],

Cell["ParallelQ", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"4d33b3c3-3740-4add-8c17-fe0513968cb7"],

Cell["SeparatesQ", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"29b8b4f0-07da-4504-a381-26a9ba52ebdb"],

Cell["FindShellParameters", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"fa8ccb26-642f-4b9e-ba42-8a2bcb05e60d"],

Cell["UniqueSegmentQ", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"bab7ce02-6ee6-4640-8711-99fd26c3a43a"],

Cell["Constructions", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"7fdf12c0-4501-4902-8d54-8cbbff3bd569"],

Cell["FindMidpoint", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"0c962298-d2ed-47cd-8f1a-0eed1311116d"],

Cell["FindPerpendicular", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"7cc689df-04fa-493e-9656-8e79d499a27c"],

Cell["FindBisectingHyperplane", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"edfff49b-6cbe-4ed9-8238-77fe2703b5a7"],

Cell["CompleteEquilateralTriangle", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"60864966-25af-4454-8dd8-7e6104123238"],

Cell["InfraAngle", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"9afa1893-c250-4caf-8588-93978863fd4d"],

Cell["SegmentLineAngle", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"91f4da1c-4009-437a-9644-5323df4e70bb"],

Cell["Method axis (FindSegment / FindLine / ExtendSegment)", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"27b48369-6b63-49c0-b856-fb660bad3d7a"],

Cell["\<\
All three share the same allow-list and pass sub-options through the Method \
spec.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"73212ad6-60ec-45fc-94d2-0f5feb1d7e57"],

Cell["\<\
\"Shortest\" (default) -- enumerate geodesics via the built-in shortest-path \
machinery.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"9da07f03-6b75-4140-9443-148916a7efee"],

Cell["\<\
\"ShortestPathExtension\" / {\"ShortestPathExtension\", \
\"ShortestPathWindow\" -> K, \"Pruning\" -> spec} -- recency-lex frontier \
sweep over simple paths; K = 1 = no filter, K = 2 (default) excludes triangle \
shortcuts, K = All compares against every predecessor.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"1001daa4-4927-4f72-adae-2606cb6f7fc0"],

Cell["\<\
\"CurvatureMinimizing\" / {\"CurvatureMinimizing\", \"Curvature\" -> spec, \
\"Pool\" -> p, \"Pruning\" -> q} -- the rope-pulled-tight sweep that \
minimises an edge-level curvature at every step.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"819630ca-52df-4ae4-a2f3-d086da7926ae"],

Cell["\<\
\"Embedding\" / {\"Embedding\", \"Coordinates\" -> coords, \"Pool\" -> p, \
\"Pruning\" -> spec} -- ranks candidate paths by Hausdorff distance to the \
straight Euclidean segment p1 p2 under the graph drawing.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"60dd6b4c-a7a2-4564-8c91-bf1a01ee8559"],

Cell["Curvature spec (under \"CurvatureMinimizing\")", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"3b9cc552-73b4-4fad-bdb4-deb491e64a63"],

Cell["\<\
\"Forman\" / {\"Forman\", Method -> \"Simple\" | \"Triangles\"} -- forwards \
Method to FormanRicci.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"64ba94eb-e0e7-4e30-b358-d2f7e5f170f3"],

Cell["\<\
\"Wolfram\" / {\"Wolfram\", \"Dimension\" -> Automatic | d, \"Radii\" -> \
Automatic | {rmin, rmax}} -- forwards options to WolframRicci.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"7ea03286-f8f4-4fa7-b38d-14fd590443e6"],

Cell["Pool values (context-dependent)", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"9a17e416-a75f-49cb-8ebf-d5d0a86b1207"],

Cell["\<\
Path-shaped consumers (FindSegment / FindLine / ExtendSegment / FindMidpoint \
/ FindPerpendicular): \"ShortestPaths\" (default; restrict to the geodesic \
DAG / metric interval) or \"AllPaths\" (full adjacency).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"64c5e60f-061c-401b-ba8b-aca79b74cd41"],

Cell["\<\
Shell-shaped consumers (FindShell / FindCircle / FindParallel): \"LevelSet\" \
(default; restrict to the metric level surface) or \"AllVertices\" (full \
vertex set).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"c934971b-1ca5-4e50-828a-2c6a253a7a15"],

Cell["Path-space post-filters", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"76798be2-2550-4ee2-b44c-1aa61d4f7189"],

Cell["\<\
Pipe Find* output through the path-space selectors to keep the central / \
peripheral / embedding-closest representatives.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"23f8a993-d6e0-4c93-9412-815e554aa7a4"],

Cell["SelectPaths (criteria: \"Central\", \"Peripheral\")", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"173b18f5-6b85-4844-bbef-4d4dbd135eb3"],

Cell["EmbeddingClosestPaths", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"5893fd4a-64ee-416f-81ba-8a49badd4038"],

Cell["Tutorial", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"be534904-f79d-49a9-9ce6-1611f2287d23"],

Cell["\<\
See EuclideanGeometryTutorial for runnable examples on paths and grids.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"0c2f1489-eaf8-4b00-9c5e-57db1f5d5b4a"],

Cell["References", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"bc3d8fc0-0e60-471b-8799-3c9735ffc191"],

Cell["\<\
Euclid, Elements (Heath translation, three volumes), Dover 1956, \
https://archive.org/details/euclid_heath_2nd_ed\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"4a99c641-942d-454a-a892-b625be7ae05c"],

Cell["\<\
Hilbert, The Foundations of Geometry, Open Court 1971 (English translation of \
the 10th German edition), https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/17384\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"408dd850-78b2-488a-ba0f-eb3b2924670f"],

Cell["\<\
Greenberg, Euclidean and Non-Euclidean Geometries: Development and History, \
W. H. Freeman, 4th ed., 2008\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"99723c00-325a-4b32-aad3-cd63ecbb835d"],

Cell["\<\
Linial, Geodesic Geometry on Graphs, \
https://www.cs.huji.ac.il/~nati/PAPERS/ge_ge_gr.pdf\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"98318332-de9c-4191-809c-161fc7887501"],

Cell["\<\
Mulder, The Interval Function of a Graph, Mathematical Centre Tracts 132, \
Amsterdam 1980\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"7cdd5bfe-acc4-4d92-8ee0-b9e099485453"],

Cell["\<\
Bandelt and Mulder, Distance-Hereditary Graphs, J. Combin. Theory Ser. B 41, \
182-208, 1986\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"71045671-0ab7-4cb8-acc9-bffe64c31feb"],

Cell["\<\
Tarski and Givant, Tarski's System of Geometry, Bulletin of Symbolic Logic \
5(2), 175-214, 1999, \
https://projecteuclid.org/journals/bulletin-of-symbolic-logic/volume-5/issue-\
2/Tarskis-system-of-geometry/bsl/1182353717\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"3973c714-ac92-4263-a52f-9560a39f3081"]
},
